As an Estate Executive (Trainee), you will be responsible for the following:
- address residents’ feedback on maintenance related matters,
- manage lease and tenancy of HDB flats (e.g. checking on feedback relating to illegal sub-letting, excessive noise),
- work with lessees and tenants on compliance to mortgage loans,
- coordinate and monitor car park improvement works, and&nbsp;
- involve in projects like estate renewal projects (e.g. HIP, LUP).&nbsp;

You should possess the following competencies/ qualities:
- effective communication skills,
- a passion to serve,
- the ability to work independently,
- confidence and assertiveness, and&nbsp;
- a willingness to learn.&nbsp;



Please note that only shortlisted candidates will be notified.